description:
Welcome to the first stage of the coordination process in graduate studies!

In this stage, you will need to select the academic program you wish to pursue, whether it is for a master's degree or a doctoral degree. After that, you will need to choose the appropriate college or center and department. If there are specializations within the department, you should specify the specialization that aligns with your interests and goals.

The goal of this stage is to guide you in making the appropriate decisions based on your personal interests and goals. This step will help you determine the academic direction you desire and identify the field of study and specialization you wish to pursue.

Please choose from the available options and select the academic program that suits you. Then, choose the college or center, department, and specialization if applicable in each department.
